{
  "stem": "3475.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were probably considered secular, you know.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were some people that, you know, they were Hasidim, you know, with the, you know, long beards and-- but it was mostly secular.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we used to play soccer, you know, which is-- we used to call it football-- a lot on the fields.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The neighborhood that we lived, it was not far from a big, empty space.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It used to be called [NON-ENGLISH] in, in Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we used to spend a lot of time there playing.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Also there were a lot of parks.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Park Traugutta, you know, was over there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So as I remember from my childhood, a lot of games, and playing, and chases, and all this kind of stuff.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I went to school-- for a while I went to a Jewish school, which was [NON-ENGLISH] school, you know, the grade school.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I guess they couldn't afford it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they sent me to a-- my parents send me to a regular grade school.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was mostly Christian.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were only about three or four Jews in the class, in that school.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that's-- and that wasn't very pleasant because--",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--we used to get beat up all the time by the Polacks.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They could--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh yeah, many times.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "After a while, we kind of learned to be tolerated.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But every once in a while when a new boy would come in, he had to, you know, start beating up Jewish kids, you know.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were mostly-- the Polack-- Polish kids were bigger than we were because they, they were older, you know.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, mostly they would say, [SPEAKING POLISH], which means you lousy Jew, you know.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, and as a matter of fact, it comes to my mind now that they used to teach catechism there.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
